unittitle_ssm: Associated Actors and Artistes of America Records
abstract_ssm: The Associated Actors and Artistes of America was founded in 1919 as an umbrella organization composed of nine autonomous performing arts unions. The main purpose of the Four A's since its founding has been to represent the affiliates' common interests and to resolve jurisdictional problems. These records include the Four A's constitutions, correspondence, financial records and meeting minutes.
